# Emotion Detection App

A simple and effective web application that detects human emotions from text input using machine learning and deep learning techniques.

This project focuses on building a practical NLP pipeline — from text preprocessing to real-time emotion prediction — and presenting it through an interactive interface.

---

## Overview

Understanding emotions from text is an important problem in areas like mental health analysis, chatbots, and user experience systems.

In this project, I built an emotion detection system that:
- Processes raw text input
- Converts it into numerical features
- Predicts the most likely emotion using trained models

The application is deployed locally using Streamlit for quick interaction and testing.

---

## Features

- Real-time emotion prediction from user input  
- Combination of Machine Learning and Deep Learning models  
- Clean and simple user interface  
- Efficient text preprocessing using NLP techniques  
- Lightweight and easy to run locally  

---

## Tech Stack

- Python  
- Streamlit  
- Scikit-learn  
- TensorFlow / Keras  
- NLTK  

